            <h1>Variance-Covariance Matrix</h1>
            <p>This lesson explains how to use matrix methods to generate a=
=20
        variance-covariance matrix from a matrix of raw data.</p>
           =20
    <h2>Variance</h2>
    <p><strong>Variance</strong> is a measure of the variability or spread =
in=20
        a set of data.
        Mathematically, it is the average squared=20
        deviation from the mean score. We use the following formula
        to compute population variance.</p>
       =20
    <p style=3D"text-align:center;">
        Var(<i>X</i>) =3D=20
        =CE=A3 ( <i>X</i><sub>i</sub> -=20
        <span class=3D"Over"><i>X</i></span> )<sup>2</sup> / <i>N</i> =3D
        =CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>i</sub><sup>2</sup> / <i>N</i>
    </p>   =20
	=09
	<p>where</p>=20
           =20
    <p style=3D"padding-left:20px;">
        <i>N</i> is the number of scores in a set of scores<br>
        <span class=3D"Over"><i>X</i></span> is the=20
        <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?definition=3D=
Mean">mean</a>
        of the <i>N</i> scores.<br>
        <i>X</i><sub>i</sub> is the <i>i</i>th raw score in the set of scor=
es<br>
        <i>x</i><sub>i</sub> is the <i>i</i>th deviation score in the set o=
f=20
            scores<br>
        Var(<i>X</i>) is the variance of all the scores in the set
    </p>

    <h2>Covariance</h2>
    <p><strong>Covariance</strong> is a measure of the extent to which=20
        corresponding elements from two sets of ordered data move in the sa=
me direction. =20
        We use the following formula to compute population covariance.</p>
       =20
    <p style=3D"text-align:center;">
        Cov(<i>X</i>, <i>Y</i>) =3D=20
        =CE=A3 ( <i>X</i><sub>i</sub> - <span class=3D"Over"><i>X</i></span=
> )=20
        ( <i>Y</i><sub>i</sub> - <span class=3D"Over"><i>Y</i></span> ) / <=
i>N</i>=20
        =3D =CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>i</sub><i>y</i><sub>i</sub> / <i>N</i>
    </p>   =20
	=09
	<p>where</p>=20
           =20
    <p style=3D"padding-left:20px;">
        <i>N</i> is the number of scores in each set of data<br>
        <span class=3D"Over"><i>X</i></span> is the=20
        <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?definition=3D=
Mean">mean</a>
        of the <i>N</i> scores in the first dataset<br>
        <i>X</i><sub>i</sub> is the <i>i</i>the raw score in the first set =
of=20
            scores<br>
        <i>x</i><sub>i</sub> is the <i>i</i>th deviation score in the first=
 set of=20
            scores<br>
        <span class=3D"Over"><i>Y</i></span> is the=20
        <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?definition=3D=
Mean">mean</a>
        of the <i>N</i> scores in the second dataset<br>
        <i>Y</i><sub>i</sub> is the <i>i</i>the raw score in the second set=
=20
            of scores<br>
        <i>y</i><sub>i</sub> is the <i>i</i>th deviation score in the secon=
d set of=20
            scores<br>
        Cov(<i>X</i>, <i>Y</i>) is the covariance of corresponding scores i=
n the=20
            two sets of data
    </p>

    <div class=3D"ad_Content">


    <!-- Ezoic - incontent1 - under_first_paragraph -->
	<div id=3D"ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-198"></div>
	<!-- End Ezoic - incontent1 - under_first_paragraph -->
</div>
    <h2>Variance-Covariance Matrix</h2>
    <p>Variance and covariance are often displayed together in a=20
        variance-covariance=20
        <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?definition=3D=
Matrix">matrix</a>,=20
        (aka, a covariance matrix).=20
        The variances appear along the diagonal and=20
        covariances appear in the off-diagonal elements, as shown below.</p=
>
   =20
    <table style=3D"margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
        <tbody><tr>
        <td>
            <strong>V</strong>&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>
            <table style=3D"margin-right:auto; margin-left:auto;">
                <tbody><tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdleftbracket" rowspan=3D"4"></td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>1</sub><=
sup>2</sup> / N&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>1</sub>&=
nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>2</sub> / N&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>1</sub>&=
nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>c</sub> / N</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdrightbracket" rowspan=3D"4"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>2</sub>&=
nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>1</sub> / N&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>2</sub><=
sup>2</sup> / N&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>2</sub>&=
nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>c</sub> / N</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>c</sub>&=
nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>1</sub> / N&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>c</sub>&=
nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>2</sub> / N&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">. . .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">=CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>c</sub><=
sup>2</sup> / N</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody></table>
        </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody></table>
   =20
    <p>where</p>=20
   =20
    <p style=3D"padding-left:20px;">
        <strong>V</strong> is a <i>c</i> x <i>c</i> variance-covariance mat=
rix<br>
        N is the number of scores in each of the <i>c</i> datasets<br>
        <i>x</i><sub>i</sub> is a=20
            <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?definitio=
n=3DDeviation_score">deviation score</a>
            from the <i>ith</i> dataset<br>
        =CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>i</sub><sup>2</sup> / N is the variance of elem=
ents from the
            <i>i</i>th dataset<br>
        =CE=A3 <i>x</i><sub>i</sub>&nbsp;<i>x</i><sub>j</sub> / N is the co=
variance for=20
            elements from the <i>i</i>th and <i>j</i>th datasets
    </p>
   =20
    <h2>How to Create a Variance-Covariance Matrix</h2>
   =20
    <p>Suppose <strong>X</strong> is an <i>n</i>&nbsp;x&nbsp;<i>k</i> matri=
x
        holding ordered sets of raw data. =20
        For example, matrix <strong>X</strong> might display the scores=20
        on <i>k</i> tests for <i>n</i> students, as shown in=20
        <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/matrix-algebra/covariance-matrix#Pr=
oblem1">Problem 1</a>.</p>
   =20
    <p>Starting with the raw data of matrix <strong>X</strong>,=20
        you can create a variance-covariance matrix to
        show the variance within each column and the covariance between col=
umns.
        Here's how.</p>
       =20
    <ul>
        <li><p>Transform the raw scores from matrix <strong>X</strong>
            into deviation scores for matrix <strong>x</strong>.</p>
   =20
            <p style=3D"text-align:center;">
                <strong>x</strong> =3D=20
                <strong>X</strong> -
                <strong>1</strong><strong>1</strong>'<strong>X</strong>
                ( 1 / n )
            </p>
           =20
            <p>where</p>=20
           =20
            <p style=3D"padding-left:20px;">
                <strong>1</strong> is an <i>n</i> x <i>1</i> column =20
                    <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?d=
efinition=3DVectors">vector</a>
                    of ones<br>
                <strong>1</strong>' is the <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/=
statistics/dictionary?definition=3Dtranspose">transpose</a> of vector <b>1<=
/b><br>
                <strong>x</strong> is an <i>n</i> x <i>k</i> matrix=20
                    of <i>deviation</i> scores: <i>x</i><sub>1</sub><sub>1<=
/sub>,=20
                    <i>x</i><sub>1</sub><sub>2</sub>, . . . ,
                    <i>x</i><sub>n</sub><sub>k</sub><br>
                <strong>X</strong> is an <i>n</i> x <i>k</i> matrix=20
                    of <i>raw</i> scores: <i>X</i><sub>1</sub><sub>1</sub>,=
=20
                    <i>X</i><sub>1</sub><sub>2</sub>, . . . ,
                    <i>X</i><sub>n</sub><sub>k</sub>
            </p></li>
        <li><p>Compute <strong>x</strong>'<strong>x</strong>, the <i>k</i> =
x <i>k</i>
            deviation sums of squares and cross products matrix for=20
            <strong>x</strong>.</p></li>
        <li><p>Then, divide each term in the deviation sums of squares and =
cross product=20
            matrix by <i>n</i> to create the variance-covariance matrix. =
=20
            That is,</p>
            <p style=3D"text-align:center;">
                <strong>V</strong> =3D=20
                <strong>x</strong>'<strong>x</strong> ( 1 / n )
            </p>
   =20
            <p>where</p>=20
           =20
            <p style=3D"padding-left:20px;">
                <strong>V</strong> is a <i>k</i> x <i>k</i> variance-covari=
ance matrix<br>
                <strong>x</strong>' is the <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/=
statistics/dictionary?definition=3Dtranspose">transpose</a> of matrix <b>x<=
/b><br>
                <strong>x</strong>'<strong>x</strong>=20
                is the deviation sums of squares and cross product matrix<b=
r>
                n is the number of scores in each column of the original ma=
trix
                <strong>X</strong>
            </p></li>
    </ul>
   =20
    <p>In the next section, read <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/matrix-alg=
ebra/covariance-matrix#Problem1">Problem 1</a>=20
        for an example showing how to turn raw data into a=20
        variance-covariance matrix.</p>
       =20
    <div class=3D"ad_Content">


    <!-- Ezoic - incontent1 - under_first_paragraph -->
	<div id=3D"ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-198"></div>
	<!-- End Ezoic - incontent1 - under_first_paragraph -->
</div>
    <a name=3D"Problem1"></a>
    <h2>Test Your Understanding</h2>
   =20
    <p><strong>Problem 1</strong></p>
   =20
    <p>The table below displays scores on math, English, and art tests
        for 5 students.</p>
       =20
    <table class=3D"table1" style=3D"max-width:300px;">
        <tbody><tr>
            <th style=3D"padding: .25rem">Student</th>
            <th style=3D"padding: .25rem">Math</th>
            <th style=3D"padding: .25rem">English</th>
            <th style=3D"padding: .25rem">Art</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">1</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">90</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">60</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">90</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">2</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">90</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">90</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">30</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">3</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">60</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">60</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">60</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">4</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">60</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">60</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">90</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">5</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">30</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">30</td>
            <td style=3D"padding: .5rem">30</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody></table>

    <p>Note that data from the table can be represented in
        matrix <strong>A</strong>, where each column in the matrix shows sc=
ores
        on a test and each row shows scores for a student.</p>
       =20
    <table style=3D"margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
        <tbody><tr>
            <td style=3D"text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; ">
                <strong>A</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;&nbsp;
            </td>
            <td style=3D"vertical-align:bottom;">
                <table style=3D"margin-right:auto; margin-left:auto;">
                <tbody><tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdleftbracket" rowspan=3D"5"></td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdrightbracket" rowspan=3D"5"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">30</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">30</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">30</td>
                    <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">30</td>
                </tr>
                </tbody></table>
            </td>
        </tr>
        </tbody></table>
   =20
    <p>Given the data represented in matrix <strong>A</strong>,=20
        compute the variance of each test and the covariance between the te=
sts.</p>

    <p><strong>Solution</strong></p>
    <p>The solution involves a three-step process.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>First, we transform the <i>raw</i> scores in matrix <strong>A</=
strong>
            to <i>deviation</i> scores in matrix <strong>a</strong>,=20
            using the transformation formula described at  =20
        <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/matrix-algebra/deviation-score">
        how to transform raw scores to deviation scores</a>.
       =20
    <p style=3D"text-align:center;">
        <strong>a</strong> =3D =20
        <strong>A</strong> -
        <strong>1</strong><strong>1</strong>'<strong>A</strong>
        ( 1 / n )
    </p>=20
   =20
    <p>where</p>=20
   =20
    <p style=3D"padding-left:20px;">
        <strong>1</strong> is an <i>5</i> x <i>1</i> column =20
            <a href=3D"https://stattrek.com/statistics/dictionary?definitio=
n=3DVectors">vector</a>
            of ones<br>
        <strong>a</strong> is an <i>5</i> x <i>3</i> matrix=20
            of <i>deviation</i> scores: <i>a</i><sub>1</sub><sub>1</sub>,=
=20
            <i>a</i><sub>1</sub><sub>2</sub>, . . . ,
            <i>a</i><sub>5</sub><sub>3</sub><br>
        <strong>A</strong> is an <i>5</i> x <i>3</i> matrix=20
            of <i>raw</i> scores: <i>A</i><sub>1</sub><sub>1</sub>,=20
            <i>A</i><sub>1</sub><sub>2</sub>, . . . ,
            <i>A</i><sub>5</sub><sub>3</sub><br>
        <i>n</i> is the number of rows in matrix <strong>A</strong>
    </p></li>
    </ul>
   =20
    <div style=3D"display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; justify-content:center;">
        <table style=3D"margin: .1rem; align-self:center;">
            <tbody><tr>
                <td><strong>a</strong></td>
                <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody></table>
        <table style=3D"margin: .1rem; align-self:center;">
            <tbody><tr>
                <td class=3D"tdleftbracket" rowspan=3D"5"></td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                <td class=3D"tdrightbracket" rowspan=3D"5"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">90</td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">30</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
                <td class=3D"tdmatrixcell">60</td>
